The White House has transmitted to Congress an amendment to the Agreement between the United States and the United Kingdom for Cooperation on the Uses of Atomic Energy for Mutual Defense Purposes. The amendment extends provisions of the agreement for 10 years and includes revisions to ensure consistency with current policies and practices. The United States believes it is in its national interest to assist the United Kingdom in maintaining a credible nuclear deterrent, given their commitment to NATO. The President has approved the amendment and urges Congress to give it favorable consideration.